content.title: Russian Oil Tanker Turns Back Under U.S. Sanctions Threat
content.summary: A Russian oil tanker bound for India has reversed course in the Baltic Sea following new U.S. sanctions on Rosneft and Lukoil, disrupting crude flows but raising doubts about the long-term impact on global oil markets.

content.title: Indian Refiners Pause Russian Oil Orders as U.S. Sanctions Bite
content.summary: Indian refiners have suspended new Russian crude orders amid tightening U.S. sanctions, awaiting government guidance on how to proceed without violating payment restrictions.

content.title: Sanctioned Russian Oil Will Find New Ways to Flow
content.summary: It will take months for Russia to find ways to evade new U.S. sanctions.  Brent crude rose by around $5 this week to $66 a barrel after the U.S. sanctioned Russian oil producers Rosneft and Lukoil.  The move will disrupt supply to Moscow’s top energy customers, China and India.
